_:Nc5398cba9d7746b3b2e65c21a45aed36 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Louise Haigh was the Secretary of State for Transport from 5 July 2024 to 29 November 2024.</p>\n\n<p>She was the youngest female Cabinet Minister to ever be appointed.  </p>\n\n<p>Louise was elected as the <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr> for Sheffield Heeley in May 2015.  </p>\n\n<p>Since being elected as an <abbr title=\"Member of Parliament\">MP</abbr>, Louise has held a number of shadow ministerial roles, including Shadow Secretary of State for Transport from 2021 to 2024.  </p>\n\n<p>Louise served as a Special Constable in the Met Police between 2009 and 2011 and worked for Aviva as a public policy manager from 2012 to 2015. </p>\n\n<p>Louise studied politics at Nottingham University and law at Birkbeck, University of London.</p>\n\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
_:N390fea74ebe94bf28390cfeda3648ca6 <http://schema.org/itemListElement> _:N9c88667baf2242ad9828775eb38b1ef3 <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/louise-haigh> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "Louise Haigh was the Secretary of State for Transport from 5 July 2024 to 29 November 2024. She was the youngest female Cabinet Minister to ever be appointed.   Louise was elected as the MP for Sheffield Heeley in May 2015.   Since being elected as an MP , Louise has held a number of shadow ministerial roles, including Shadow Secretary of State for Transport from 2021 to 2024.   Louise served as a Special Constable in the Met Police between 2009 and 2011 and worked for Aviva as a public policy manager from 2012 to 2015.  Louise studied politics at Nottingham University and law at Birkbeck, University of London."@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/people/louise-haigh> <http://ogp.me/ns#site_name> "GOV.UK"@en <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/rdfa> .
